params._data: Byte data of function to call in module

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._exchanges: Array of exchanges mapping to correct component, uint256 used to signify exchange

params._coolOffPeriods: Array of cool off periods to correct component

params._tradeMaximums: Array of trade maximums mapping to correct component

params._newComponents: Array of new components to add to allocation
params._newComponentsTargetUnits: Array of target units at end of rebalance for new components, maps to same index of component
params._oldComponentsTargetUnits: Array of target units at end of rebalance for old component, maps to same index of component,                                              if component being removed set to 0.
params._positionMultiplier: Position multiplier when target units were calculated, needed in order to adjust target units                                              if fees accrued

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params._status: Boolean indicating if anyone can trade

params._statuses: Booleans indicating if matching trader can trade
params._traders: Array trader addresses to toggle status

accrueFeeAndDistribute().notice: Accrue fees from streaming fee module and transfer tokens to operator / methodologist addresses based on fee split

addModule(address).notice: OPERATOR ONLY: Add a new module to the SetToken.

interactModule(address,bytes).notice: OPERATOR ONLY: Interact with a module registered on the SetToken. Cannot be used to call functions in the fee module, due to ability to bypass methodologist permissions to update streaming fee.

removeModule(address).notice: OPERATOR ONLY: Remove a new module from the SetToken.

setAssetExchanges(address[],uint256[]).notice: OPERATOR ONLY: Set exchange for passed components

setCoolOffPeriods(address[],uint256[]).notice: OPERATOR ONLY: Set exchange for passed components

setTimeLockPeriod(uint256).notice: OPERATOR OR METHODOLOGIST ONLY: Update the timelock period for updating the streaming fee percentage. Operator and Methodologist must each call this function to execute the update.

setTradeMaximums(address[],uint256[]).notice: OPERATOR ONLY: Set trade maximums for passed components

startRebalance(address[],uint256[],uint2.notice: OPERATOR ONLY: Start rebalance in IndexModule. Set new target units, zeroing out any units for components being removed from index. Log position multiplier to adjust target units in case fees are accrued.

updateAnyoneTrade(bool).notice: OPERATOR ONLY: Toggle whether anyone can trade, bypassing the traderAllowList

updateFeeRecipient(address).notice: OPERATOR OR METHODOLOGIST ONLY: Update the fee recipient address. Operator and Methodologist must each call this function to execute the update.

updateFeeSplit(uint256).notice: OPERATOR OR METHODOLOGIST ONLY: Update the fee split percentage. Operator and Methodologist must each call this function to execute the update.

updateIndexModule(address).notice: OPERATOR ONLY: Update the index module

updateManager(address).notice: OPERATOR OR METHODOLOGIST ONLY: Update the SetToken manager address. Operator and Methodologist must each call this function to execute the update.

updateMethodologist(address).notice: METHODOLOGIST ONLY: Update the methodologist address

updateOperator(address).notice: OPERATOR ONLY: Update the operator address

updateStreamingFee(uint256).notice: METHODOLOGIST ONLY: Update the streaming fee for the SetToken. Subject to timelock period agreed upon by the operator and methodologist

updateTraderStatus(address[],bool[]).notice: OPERATOR ONLY: Toggle ability for passed addresses to trade from current state
